main event: Observers noted three objects traveling fast and abruptly changing direction and speed as they moved across the sky.
interesting points: The event occurred on 30 July 1966, at 0130Z,The location of the sighting was Cheltenham, Pennsylvania,There were three objects observed during the sighting,The conclusion by the Air Force was that the objects were aircraft,The objects did not match conventional aircraft characteristics.
witness description: The witness was 22 or 24 years old and reported seeing the objects with friends.
